{"id":2,"date":"2023-09-12T18:39:08","date_gmt":"2023-09-12T18:39:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/?page_id=2"},"modified":"2024-11-06T03:08:12","modified_gmt":"2024-11-06T03:08:12","slug":"sample-page","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/","title":{"rendered":"Welcome to the 3D Information for Perception and Action Lab!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized is-style-default\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-511\" style=\"width:842px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-200x133.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222-660x440.jpg 660w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2024\/11\/CoPsy-3DIPA-Lab_4L9A1222.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:56px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We study how the human visual system processes visual information to allow successful interactions with the environment. Our approach is to combine computational methods and behavioral studies to understand what are the visual features that establish the mapping between vision and action. Contrary to the commonly held assumption that perception and action stem from separate visual mechanisms, we take a fundamentally different view, proposing that perception and action form a coordinated system: Perception informs action about the state of the world and, in turn, action shapes perception by signaling when it is faulty. Through this integrated approach, quite distinct from most investigations on perception and motor control, we seek understanding:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/research\/#Visual_encoding_of_3D_object_properties\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/research\/\">Visual encoding of 3D object properties<\/a>: What are the visual signals that reflect these properties, how are these signals analyzed across disparate viewing conditions, what are the computational mechanisms that model these processes, and how well do these models predict perceptual performance?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/research\/#Visuomotor_mapping\">Visuomotor mapping<\/a>: How is the 3D visual encoding transformed into motor actions? What is the role of feedback during an action?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/research\/#Plasticity_of_the_motor_mapping_and_visual_encoding_of_3D_information\">Plasticity of the motor mapping and visual encoding of 3D information<\/a>: How do motor actions adapt to faulty visual information? Is it sufficient to change the visuomotor mapping? Or does the very perceptual interpretation of the environment need to be reshaped?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:150px\"><div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-medium is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"117\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/Logo_lab-e1695741967221-300x117.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-70\" style=\"width:164px;height:64px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/Logo_lab-e1695741967221-300x117.png 300w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/Logo_lab-e1695741967221-768x300.png 768w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/Logo_lab-e1695741967221-800x312.png 800w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/Logo_lab-e1695741967221.png 1000w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:150px\"><div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-medium is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.brown.edu\/academics\/cognitive-linguistic-psychological-sciences\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"69\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner-300x69.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-69\" style=\"width:160px;height:36px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner-300x69.png 300w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner-1024x237.png 1024w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner-768x178.png 768w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner-1536x355.png 1536w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/logo_clps-banner.png 1856w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:130px\"><div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.brown.edu\/carney\/centers-initiatives\/center-vision-research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"246\" height=\"142\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/CVR.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-352\" style=\"width:109px;height:63px\"\/><\/a><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:70px\"><div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.nsf.gov\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"220\" height=\"221\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/NSF_logo.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\" style=\"width:62px;height:62px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/NSF_logo.png 220w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/NSF_logo-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/NSF_logo-140x140.png 140w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" \/><\/a><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100px\"><div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1002\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/oculus.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-354\" style=\"width:109px;height:61px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/oculus.png 1002w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/oculus-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/sites.brown.edu\/3dipalab\/files\/2023\/09\/oculus-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1002px) 100vw, 1002px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We study how the human visual system processes visual information to allow successful interactions with t